cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the problem of offline handwritten Chinese character recognition using deep learning methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as attention mechanism and recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of DenseNet as an encoder and the proposed DenseRAN architecture indicate that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the recognition of unseen Chinese character classes, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
